,1.2070802342991265,1.2070686291710289,1.2070570736006094,1.2070455673762397,1.207034110287197,1.2070227021236561,1.2070113426766895,1.207000031738263,1.206988769101228,1.206977554559322,1.2069663879071637,1.2069552689402467,1.2069441974549413,1.2069331732484845,1.206922196118981,1.206911265865396,1.2069003822875553,1.2068895451861366,1.2068787543626718,1.2068680096195374,1.2068573107599572,1.206846657587993,1.2068360499085427,1.2068254875273396,1.2068149702509454,1.206804497886748,1.2067940702429563,1.2067836871286013,1.2067733483535261,1.2067630537283898,1.2067528030646546,1.206742596174594,1.206732432871278,1.2067223129685793,1.206712236281161,1.2067022026244811,1.2066922118147838,1.2066822636690981,1.2066723580052359,1.2066624946417843,1.2066526733981089,1.206642894094343,1.2066331565513897,1.2066234605909174,1.206613806035354,1.206604192707888,1.2065946204324625,1.2065850890337715,1.2065755983372572,1.20656614816911,1.2065567383562583,1.2065473687263721,1.2065380391078597,1.2065287493298562,1.2065194992222312,1.2065102886155796,1.2065011173412183,1.2064919852311873,1.20648289211824,1.206473837835848,1.2064648222181908,1.2064558451001577,1.206446906317343,1.2064380057060429,1.2064291431032532,1.2064203183466649,1.206411531274661,1.2064027817263174,1.2063940695413948,1.2063853945603404,1.2063767566242818,1.206368155575024],\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"lines\",\"line\":{\"color\":\"darkorange\",\"width\":2},\"name\":\"lines\"}],\"layout\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Training Loss (MSE/2)\"},\"width\":700,\"height\":450,\"plot_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"xaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Iteration\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1},\"yaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Loss\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1}}}"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 2. Logistic Regression\n\n### Symbolic Phase: Sigmoid and Cross-Entropy Gradient\n\nThe sigmoid function $\\sigma(z) = \\frac{1}{1 + e^{-z}}$ is the key building block. Its derivative has a remarkably clean form:",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic sigmoid and its derivative */\nsigma(z) := 1 / (1 + exp(-z))$\n\nsigma_deriv : diff(sigma(z), z);\nsigma_deriv_simplified : ratsimp(sigma_deriv);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 114,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "%e^-z/(%e^-z+1)^2"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "{{e^{z}}\\over{e^{2\\,z}+2\\,e^{z}+1}}"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 114,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Verify: sigma'(z) = sigma(z) * (1 - sigma(z)) */\nis(ratsimp(sigma_deriv - sigma(z) * (1 - sigma(z))) = 0);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 115,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\mathbf{true}"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 115,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "The binary cross-entropy loss for one sample is:\n\n$$\\ell_i = -\\left[ y_i \\log \\sigma(z_i) + (1 - y_i) \\log(1 - \\sigma(z_i)) \\right]$$\n\nwhere $z_i = w_0 + w_1 x_{i1} + w_2 x_{i2}$. The gradient of the loss with respect to $w$ turns out to be:\n\n$$\\nabla_w L = \\frac{1}{N} X^T (\\sigma(Xw) - y)$$\n\nwhich has the same form as linear regression but with $\\sigma(Xw)$ replacing $Xw$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic verification: gradient of cross-entropy */\nell(z, yi) := -(yi * log(sigma(z)) + (1 - yi) * log(1 - sigma(z)))$\n\n/* d(ell)/dz simplifies to sigma(z) - y */\ndell_dz : diff(ell(z, yi), z)$\nratsimp(dell_dz);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 116,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "-\\left({{\\left(e^{z}+1\\right)\\,{\\it yi}-e^{z}}\\over{e^{z}+1}}\\right)"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 116,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "The symbolic computation confirms: $\\frac{\\partial \\ell}{\\partial z} = \\sigma(z) - y$, so the full gradient is $\\nabla_w L = \\frac{1}{N} X^T (\\hat{y} - y)$.\n\n### Numeric Phase: Binary Classification",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Generate 2D binary classification data */\nn_class : 60$\nn_total : 2 * n_class$\n\n/* Class 0: centred at (-1, -1) */\nx0_1 : np_add(np_randn([n_class]), -1.0)$\nx0_2 : np_add(np_randn([n_class]), -1.0)$\n\n/* Class 1: centred at (1.5, 1.5) */\nx1_1 : np_add(np_randn([n_class]), 1.5)$\nx1_2 : np_add(np_randn([n_class]), 1.5)$\n\n/* Stack features into design matrix [n_total, 3] with bias column */\nX0 : np_hstack(np_ones([n_class, 1]),\n               np_reshape(x0_1, [n_class, 1]),\n               np_reshape(x0_2, [n_class, 1]))$\nX1 : np_hstack(np_ones([n_class, 1]),\n               np_reshape(x1_1, [n_class, 1]),\n               np_reshape(x1_2, [n_class, 1]))$\nX_lr : np_vstack(X0, X1)$\n\n/* Labels */\ny_lr : np_reshape(\n  ndarray(append(makelist(0.0, i, 1, n_class), makelist(1.0, i, 1, n_class))),\n  [n_total, 1]\n)$\n\nprint(\"Data shape:\", np_shape(X_lr), \"Labels:\", np_shape(y_lr))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 117,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Data shape: [120,3] Labels: [120,1]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Numeric sigmoid function on ndarrays */\nnp_sigmoid(z) := np_div(1.0, np_add(1.0, np_exp(np_neg(z))))$\n\n/* Logistic regression via gradient descent */\nw_lr : np_zeros([3, 1])$\nlr_rate : 0.1$\nlr_iters : 200$\nlr_losses : []$\n\nfor iter : 1 thru lr_iters do block(\n  z : np_matmul(X_lr, w_lr),\n  p : np_sigmoid(z),\n  /* Cross-entropy loss (with clipping for stability) */\n  p_safe : np_clip(p, 1.0e-10, 1.0 - 1.0e-10),\n  loss : -np_mean(np_add(\n    np_mul(y_lr, np_log(p_safe)),\n    np_mul(np_sub(1.0, y_lr), np_log(np_sub(1.0, p_safe)))\n  )),\n  lr_losses : append(lr_losses, [loss]),\n  /* Gradient: X^T (p - y) / N */\n  grad : np_scale(1.0 / n_total, np_matmul(np_transpose(X_lr), np_sub(p, y_lr))),\n  w_lr : np_sub(w_lr, np_scale(lr_rate, grad))\n)$\n\nw0 : np_ref(w_lr, 0, 0)$\nw1 : np_ref(w_lr, 1, 0)$\nw2 : np_ref(w_lr, 2, 0)$\nprint(\"Learned weights: w0 =\", w0, \", w1 =\", w1, \", w2 =\", w2)$\nprint(\"Final loss:\", last(lr_losses))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 118,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Learned weights: w0 = -0.19317237220586753 , w1 = 1.8203826072530085 , w2 =\n                     1.372177087662403\nFinal loss: 0.12387341236873187"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### One-liner with np_minimize\n\nAgain, the manual loop can be replaced by `np_minimize`. The L-BFGS optimizer finds the same solution in fewer iterations:",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Cross-entropy cost and gradient as named functions */\nlr_cost(w) := block([z, p, p_safe],\n  z : np_matmul(X_lr, w),\n  p : np_sigmoid(z),\n  p_safe : np_clip(p, 1.0e-10, 1.0 - 1.0e-10),\n  -np_mean(np_add(\n    np_mul(y_lr, np_log(p_safe)),\n    np_mul(np_sub(1.0, y_lr), np_log(np_sub(1.0, p_safe)))\n  )))$\n\nlr_grad(w) := block([z, p],\n  z : np_matmul(X_lr, w),\n  p : np_sigmoid(z),\n  np_scale(1.0 / n_total, np_matmul(np_transpose(X_lr), np_sub(p, y_lr))))$\n\n[w_lr_opt, lr_loss_opt, lr_conv] : np_minimize(lr_cost, lr_grad, np_zeros([3, 1]))$\nprint(\"np_minimize weights:\",\n      np_ref(w_lr_opt, 0, 0), np_ref(w_lr_opt, 1, 0), np_ref(w_lr_opt, 2, 0))$\nprint(\"Loss:\", lr_loss_opt, \"  Converged:\", lr_conv)$\n\n/* Use L-BFGS solution for subsequent analysis */\nw_lr : w_lr_opt$\nw0 : np_ref(w_lr, 0, 0)$\nw1 : np_ref(w_lr, 1, 0)$\nw2 : np_ref(w_lr, 2, 0)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 119,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "*************************************************\n  N=    3   NUMBER OF CORRECTIONS= 3\n       INITIAL VALUES\n F=  6.931471805599461D-01   GNORM=  8.416947749491879D-01\n*************************************************\n   I  NFN     FUNC                    GNORM                   STEPLENGTH\n   1    2     2.444234918478491D-01   1.942251384886299D-01   1.188079134815075D+00\n  14   15     9.521970833020975D-02   1.509291796415268D-08   1.000000000000000D+00\n THE MINIMIZATION TERMINATED WITHOUT DETECTING ERRORS.\n IFLAG = 0\nnp_minimize weights: -0.3697717511342595 3.609120748276671 2.912468935181026\nLoss: 0.09521970833020975   Converged: true"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Compute accuracy */\npred_probs : np_sigmoid(np_matmul(X_lr, w_lr))$\npred_labels : np_where(np_greater(pred_probs, 0.5), 1.0, 0.0)$\ncorrect : np_sum(np_equal(pred_labels, y_lr))$\naccuracy : correct / n_total * 100$\nprint(\"Accuracy:\", accuracy, \"%\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 120,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Accuracy: 97.5 %o235"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot data with decision boundary */\nx0_1_list : np_to_list(x0_1)$\nx0_2_list : np_to_list(x0_2)$\nx1_1_list : np_to_list(x1_1)$\nx1_2_list : np_to_list(x1_2)$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color = \"steelblue\", marker_size = 6, name = \"Class 0\",\n  points(x0_1_list, x0_2_list),\n  color = \"darkorange\", marker_size = 6, name = \"Class 1\",\n  points(x1_1_list, x1_2_list),\n  color = \"red\", line_width = 2, name = \"Decision boundary\",\n  implicit(w0 + w1 * u + w2 * v = 0, u, -4, 5, v, -4, 5),\n  title = \"Logistic Regression: Decision Boundary\",\n  xlabel = \"x1\", ylabel = \"x2\", grid = true, showlegend = true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 121,
      "outputs": [
        {
